=== Etymology ===
Latin ''Pangaea'' from Greek [[παγγαία]] (pangaía), from [[πάν]] (pán) "all" + [[γή]] (gē) "[[earth]]".

===Hyphenation===
pan·gae·a

===Proper noun===
'''Pangaea'''

====Alternative spellings====
*'''Pangea''' (''mainly US'')

#A [[supercontinent]] that included all the [[landmass]]es of the [[earth]] before the [[Triassic Period]] and that broke up into [[Laurasia]] and [[Gondwanaland]].

